        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2022-07-20T16:43:39Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Ban Congressional Stock Trading Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires each Member of Congress to divest or place in a blind trust any specified investment owned by the Member, the Member's spouse, or a dependent of the Member. This requirement applies for the entire period of a Member's service in Congress and for 180 days after that service ceases.</p> <p> A Member of Congress who does not comply with the bill's requirements is subject to a fine equal to the Member's monthly congressional salary. The fine must be assessed 30 days after notice of the violation is issued and at least every subsequent 30 days.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
